<Content>This was the worst place to stay in Puerto Rico. This was the worst hotel I have ever been to. We arrived at about 6pm . And was told we had to take our own luggage to the second floor because the bellhopper had left for the day. We were also told we were to have complimentary dinner. To which the cook had also left early because he was tired. Upon dragging our luggage to the second floor with the key room and remote for the TV in hand . THe room was hidious. There as only about 5 channels to view. There was creepy looking guys roaming the halls. And upon parking the car there was people having intercourse in the parking lot. We remain a max. stay of 10 minutes, We were told to speak to the manager the following day. She was unable to resolve any problems. Do not be fooled by this stay. You have a better chance staying on the town next to it on the road 100 THE LIGHT HOUSE. THis was a fantastic place to stay. 
