<Author>MiaMobile
<Content>the worst motel on Earth!!!! I stayed in the dusty, filthy ,dirty, horrendous place due that I was looking for a place in San German, PR. First, The parking is in a lot one block away very dark w/o illumination. There is no elevators. I had to carry my luggage to the second floors by the stairs without help. The room, What a room. The carpet has not been clean since the open this motel in more than 40 yrs, is so dirty that you have to use your shoes all the time. Beds are raggidy and the mattress is old and out of shape. When I went to the bathroom is so dirty the shower that I preferred to skip a bath that night. And they had the odyssey of charging 80 dollars a night for a place that not even pigs would stay. After a horrible scary night (By the way the door has the lock broken), I left the hotel in the morning and requestes to have my second night credit to my credit card, which they refused. I assumed they charge in advanced to catch a bunch of fools like me. I told that I hope with the money of the second night they could make some repairs.I called the Mayaguez Holiday INN instead, They were happy to welcome me after this trauma and the HOLIDAY INN is a Five star hotel compared with the pigstay of OASIS. Thanks Hoilday INN.!M.Ruiz from LA 
